Customer Segmentation Analysis

ðŸ“Œ Project Overview

This project applies K-Means clustering to group customers into meaningful segments based on their demographics, purchasing behavior, and preferences.
The goal is to help businesses understand customer profiles, tailor marketing strategies, and improve customer retention.

ðŸŽ¯ Objectives

Identify distinct customer segments.
Analyze the purchasing and preference patterns of each group.
Provide actionable insights for targeted marketing.

ðŸ—‚ Dataset & Features
The dataset contains customer-related variables, including:

Feature	Description

Income	Annual income of the customer
MntTotal	Total money spent across all products
Age	Customer's age
AcceptedCmpOverall	Number of accepted marketing campaigns
PhysicalPreference	Preference for in-store shopping
OnlinePreference	Preference for online shopping
TotalPurchases	Total number of purchases made
MntRegularProducts	Amount spent on regular (non-promotional) products


ðŸ›  Methodology

1. Data Preprocessing
Handled missing values and outliers.
Scaled numerical features for better clustering performance.

2. Feature Selection
Selected relevant features based on business relevance and data availability.

3. K-Means Clustering
Determined optimal number of clusters using the Elbow Method and Silhouette Score.
Trained the K-Means model on standardized features.


ðŸ“¦ Technologies Used

Python: Data analysis and modeling

Pandas, NumPy: Data handling

Matplotlib, Seaborn: Visualization

Scikit-learn: Machine learning (K-Means, scaling)

Jupyter Notebook: Interactive analysis
